Description. Measurements. Medium-sized individuals; crown 1.7–3.6 mm long, 5–8 pairs of radioles (
Table 1
). Complete specimens with trunk 2.5– 9 mm long ( holotype longer but incomplete), 0.3-0.85 mm wide, 3–6 thoracic chaetigers (most with 4–5 ), 17–52 abdominal chaetigers (
Table 1
).

The range of variation in numbers of thoracic chaetigers is 3–6 among observed specimens (
Table 1
). This variation might reflect the consequences of regeneration subsequent to scissiparity (
Knight-Jones & Bowden 1984
;
Fitzhugh 2003
;
Nogueira & Knight-Jones 2003
;
Nogueira et al. 2004
), especially considering the amount of variation between left and half sides of the body in number of radioles and body segments, which we believe is also due to imperfect regeneration.
